                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        Personal Instalment Loan Agreement
                    </p>
                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        1. How our Loan works
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        Our Loan allows you to borrow a sum of money that you repay by regular Instalments over an
                        agreed period, with fees and interest.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You agree to only use the Loan Amount for the Purpose stated above. We reserve the right to
                        request evidence that the Loan Amount has been/is being used for the Purpose. Should we
                        determine, at our sole discretion, that the Loan Amount, or any part thereof, has not been used
                        for the Purpose, we reserve the right to cancel the Loan and demand immediate repayment of all
                        amounts disbursed under the Loan.
                    </p>
                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        2. Our Agreement
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        In the rest of these terms, we refer to:
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            this personal Loan agreement as this ‘Agreement’; and
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            your bank account with us or any other nominated bank account as ‘your Account’.
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You acknowledge that if you fail to comply with any terms and conditions mentioned as part of
                        the loan agreement or if the Loan is not used for the purpose as stated in your application, you
                        will be in default under the terms of this agreement.
                    </p>

                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        3. Your Loan amount
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You agree that your Loan will be the amount you applied for.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You agree to notify us in writing if you take up additional credit facilities with another
                        credit provider during the term of this Agreement.
                    </p>
                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        4. Receiving your Loan
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        We will disburse your Loan (or the balance after we have paid off your debt to another credit
                        provider), to your Absa bank account.

                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You are required to maintain sufficient funds in the designated account, which you have agreed
                        upon, for the monthly debiting of your loan repayments - (i) In case you have an existing Absa
                        bank account OR (ii) In case you have chosen any non-Absa bank account, from where your monthly
                        repayments are to be debited.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You authorize us to change the date on which we debit your account to pay the Instalment due to
                        a closer date on which your salary is credited to your account. Where we do so, we will notify
                        you at least 7 business days before the date upon which the change will occur.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        If we require you to pay off a debt to a credit provider as a condition of your loan, you must
                        obtain a statement for us from the credit provider showing how much is required to pay off the
                        debt, and we will give you a cheque (or make a direct payment) to the credit provider and pay or
                        make available (in case it is the earmarked amount) the remainder of your loan to you.
                    </p>
                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        5. Interest, fees and costs
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You agree to pay interest, fees and costs as stated or referred to in this agreement.
                    </p>
                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        6. Interest
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (a) We will charge you Interest on the balance outstanding of your Loan daily at the end of each
                        day. The outstanding balance comprises of the entire Loan amount disbursed, including the
                        ‘earmarked amount’ in your account as well, if applicable.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (b) We will not charge Interest on any Interest which forms part of the balance outstanding on
                        your Loan unless such Interest remains unpaid for at least 12 months.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (c) We calculate interests on your outstanding Loan amount on a daily basis and these are
                        adjusted to the loan account monthly.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (d) Unless the interest rate on your Loan is a fixed one, such interest rate will change as our
                        Reference Rate varies from time to time. The reference rate can be either our “Prime Lending
                        Rate” or the “Key Rate”.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (e) You will be notified by us, of changes in our Reference Rate and/or the margin to your
                        Interest Rate and the adjusted amount of your Instalment, within 45 days after the changes take
                        effect.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (f) If there is not enough money in your Account to pay an Instalment we will, subject to Clause
                        6(g) below, charge the default interest rate on the overdue amount until it is paid.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (g) If you default, you will pay a default interest rate of 2 per cent, wherever applicable,
                        calculated on the default instalment capital excluding interest payable thereon.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (h) If the reference rate is less than zero, the Interest shall be deemed to be zero, if
                        applicable.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (i) This clause 6(i) is applicable to you only if the Bank has granted you a special interest
                        rate because of the customer segment to which you belong at the time of the offer of the
                        facility. Should you move to another customer segment during the term of the loan, the bank
                        reserves the right to review the interest rate. If it proceeds as such: (i) all outstanding
                        amounts on your account shall bear interests at the prevailing commercial rate based on your new
                        customer segment; (ii) the loan will be re-amortised on the date you change customer segment,
                        based on the outstanding balance on the account, the new applicable interest rate, your maximum
                        debt service ratio and the remaining tenor of your Loan; (iii) your revised Instalment shall
                        then be duly communicated to you; (iv) the bank shall notify you of the changes 30 days before
                        the changes take effect.
                    </p>
