                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        7. Instalments
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You must pay the Instalments to repay your Loan. Your Instalments will be deducted from your
                        Account on a monthly basis on the agreed Instalment date.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You agree to tell us and any additional credit providers if you are unable to pay an Instalment
                        on the Instalment date (including the reason why you are not able to pay the Instalment). You
                        must seek our agreement regarding arrangements for the payment of the Instalment in default.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        If we need to change the date of your Instalment, we will notify you at least 7 business days
                        before the date upon which the change will occur.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You undertake to pay any residual balance left at the end of the Term of the Loan.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        If any sum falls due for payment on a day which is not a Business Day it shall be made on the
                        immediately preceding Business Day.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        In the event that you fail to pay the Instalment on the Instalment date, without prejudice to
                        any of our rights, we shall, at our own discretion and without any prior notice to you, be
                        entitled to place a hold on an amount, not exceeding the amount in arrears under this Agreement,
                        standing to the credit of your Account or any other account that you may hold in our books to
                        secure the payment of the amount in arrears. The Instalment amount will be debited from your
                        account in favour of the Bank as payment of the amount in arrears. The hold will be released
                        when the amount in arrears has been settled. When the Bank exercises this right, you will not be
                        able to withdraw or use the earmarked amount sitting in your account.
                    </p>
                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        8. Pre-payments and paying off your Loan early
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        At any time, you can pay Instalments early or pay off the whole outstanding balance of your
                        Loan.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        If you want to pay off the whole outstanding balance you must inform us, and we will give you a
                        statement telling you how much you owe.
                    </p>
                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        9. Insurance
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        If you have opted to choose the insurance premiums during your loan application, we will be
                        deducting the applicable one-time premium against the loan amount disbursed. If you are willing
                        to pledge any other insurance policy, it should be equal in amount and not less than the value
                        of your Loan for the term of this agreement, and you will be required to provide us with proof,
                        and that you have taken up the requisite insurance policies and you agree to pay the said
                        insurance premiums upfront for the duration of this agreement. The proceeds of the insurance
                        policies will be assigned to us.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        Pursuant to Section 81 of the Insurance Act 2005, you have a free choice as to the insurance
                        policy required to guarantee this Loan. The insurance policy to be provided can take the form of
                        (1) a new insurance policy;
                        (2) an existing insurance policy; or (3) a combination of the aforementioned two. <b>By signing
                            this Agreement, you hereby confirm that you have been informed of your right to this free
                            choice under Section 81 of the Insurance Act 2005 and that you have exercised this right
                            freely and willingly.</b>
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        In the event that you fail to renew or maintain the required insurance cover during the term of
                        this Agreement, you authorise us to pay the insurance premium on your behalf by debiting your
                        Account or your Loan account.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You will notify us of any event which may give rise to a claim under any insurance policy
                        assigned with respect to your Loan.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        <b><u>Your rights</u></b>
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (a) Request for a copy of the contract pertaining to the security signed by yourself at any time
                        on or after signature of the contract; <br />
                        (b) Make enquiries from the MCIB on information which has been registered in your name by the
                        Bank; <br />
                        (c) Make a complaint if you feel aggrieved by the acts or omissions of the Bank by calling our
                        Service Centre on the (+230) 402 1000; <br />
                        (d) Submit a request for a statement of account related to the credit facility at any time
                        during the credit facility period; and<br />
                        (e) Seek legal advice pertaining to the above security to understand the commitment and the
                        potential consequences of entering into this contract at your own cost and expenses.
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        <b><u>Your liabilities</u></b>
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (a) You have bound yourself for the Borrower’s debt and you undertake to honour the credit
                        obligations of the Borrower in case of impaired credits; <br />
                        (b) In case the Borrower fails to pay, you are liable for Borrower’s debt which may include
                        accrued interest, as specified in the contract pertaining to the security;<br />
                        (c) In case the Borrower fails to pay, you are liable for the liabilities of the Borrower
                        pertaining to the security and; <br />
                        (d) You will be rendered liable under the contract if the Borrower is in default of any payment
                        to the Bank and the Bank makes a demand on the Guarantor.
                    </p>

                    <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700;">
                        10. Default
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        You will be in default under the terms of this agreement, if and when applicable:
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (a) <b>Non-Payment:</b> you do not pay an Instalment in full by the Instalment date and such
                        failure to pay continues for a period of: <br />
                        &nbsp; (i) three (3) months if Instalments must be repaid on a monthly basis; or <br />
                        &nbsp; (ii) six (6) months if Instalments must be repaid at intervals other than on a monthly
                        basis; or
                    </p>
                    <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
                        (b) <b>Other obligations:</b> You do not comply with your obligations under any other credit
                        facilities and/or ancillary facilities agreements which you already have with us and/or which
